-- Obama: G20 steps to help economy transition to growth
-- 
-- Fri Sep 25, 2009 5:24pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/09/25/us-g20-economy-sb-idUSTRE58O6H420090925

 

 PITTSBURGH  (Reuters) - President Barack Obama on Friday said the G20 had taken significant steps to help the global economy transition to sustained growth. 

 At the end of the world leaders meeting, Obama also said the G20 had agreed to keep the stimulus until jobs return.